    {
      "id": "PopularPost298481",
      "post_content": "Looking at this now, it's not hard to understand why Rebels outclassed Mercenaries, even back in the day. While Rebels searched up, Mercenaries searched down - wherein lay the problem. Without [Dark Ritual](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Dark Ritual) and its ilk, it's hard to get the bigger Mercenaries into play in the first place, in order to look for their minions. With Rebels, the flow of the game dictates that the longer it goes, the more mana you have available. This made grabbing [Jhovall Queen](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Jhovall Queen) possible, and even without the amazing [Lin Sivvi, Defiant Hero](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Lin Sivvi, Defiant Hero), you could raise a pretty staunch army that adapted to the changing board. Grabbing a 2/2 Mercenaries, however, would not necessarily help much on turn 7.",
      "posted_by": "Equinox523",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost298481\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl02_post\">Looking at this now, it's not hard to understand why Rebels outclassed Mercenaries, even back in the day.  While Rebels searched up, Mercenaries searched down - wherein lay the problem.  Without <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Dark Ritual\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Dark Ritual\">Dark Ritual</a> and its ilk, it's hard to get the bigger Mercenaries into play in the first place, in order to look for their minions.  With Rebels, the flow of the game dictates that the longer it goes, the more mana you have available.  This made grabbing <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Jhovall Queen\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Jhovall Queen\">Jhovall Queen</a> possible, and even without the amazing <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Lin Sivvi, Defiant Hero\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Lin Sivvi, Defiant Hero\">Lin Sivvi, Defiant Hero</a>, you could raise a pretty staunch army that adapted to the changing board.  Grabbing a 2/2 Mercenaries, however, would not necessarily help much on turn 7.</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl02_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"../../Classes/Controls/#\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl02_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '298481'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                    \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                                <span id=\"PostedBy1136\">Equinox523</span>\r\n                                (2/6/2013 10:40:49 AM)\r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    Rating:\u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n<div class=\"starRating\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl02_postRating_starRating\"><img alt=\"0.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"5.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/>\n<br/>\n</div>\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    \u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n</div>"
